classes.documentation:
A contract allows an employer or agency to place job advertisements on a website. For the jobs to be shown, the website, contract and job all need to be active and current.
Contracts can be pre-paid or credit. For each active credit contract, a charge schedule can be produced at month-end.

attributes.documentation: This is the amount of sales tax in the transaction

attributes.name: TransactionType
attributes.caption: Transaction Type
attributes.documentation: {C=Credit Card,A=On Account,J=Journal}

attributes.name: Description
attributes.caption: Description
attributes.documentation: This is a text description of the transaction

attributes.name: IsCredit
attributes.caption: Is Credit
attributes.documentation: This is a copy of the IsCredit field at the time of the transaction. It is used to identify which transactions should be printed.

attributes.name: PaymentEngineCode
attributes.caption: Payment Engine Code
attributes.documentation: This is the code given by the payment engine

attributes.name: Status
attributes.caption: Status
attributes.documentation: {O=Sent to DPS,A=Accepted,R=Rejected,X=Timed-out,I=Invoiced,C=Chargeable}

attributes.name: Details
attributes.caption: Details
attributes.documentation: This is a PHP array that holds the details for posting once the payment ic cleared

classes.name: Upload Profile
classes.caption: Upload Profile
classes.documentation: This holds any details required for uploading batches of jobs.

attributes.name: IsActive
attributes.caption: Is Active
attributes.documentation: This will allow us to deactivate an upload account regardless of the status of the contract.

attributes.name: WatchDirectory
attributes.caption: Watch Directory
attributes.documentation:
This may be a file directory or an FTP directory.
It may be in the form 
ftp://user:password@hostname/directory

classes.name: Website
classes.caption: Website
classes.documentation: This is the target website. At the time of writing, there is only one. JobUniverse.co.nz

attributes.name: Name
attributes.caption: Name
attributes.documentation: This is the name of the website

attributes.name: isActive
attributes.caption: Is Active
attributes.documentation: This indicates whether the site is currently active. If not, it will not accept job adverts.

classes.name: Enhancement
classes.caption: Enhancement
classes.documentation: These are bug enhancements

attributes.name: Priority
attributes.caption: Priority
attributes.documentation: A,B or C

attributes.name: Context
attributes.caption: Context
attributes.documentation: Used to constrain the action to only be available in certain contexts.

attributes.name: SecurityLevel
attributes.caption: Security Level
attributes.documentation: Used for linking to cascading menu security

attributes.name: Name
attributes.caption: Name
attributes.documentation: This is the first name and surname of the user.

attributes.name: NetworkId
attributes.caption: Network Id
attributes.documentation: This is used for autologin across a LAN

attributes.name: EmailAddress
attributes.caption: Email Address
attributes.documentation: The email address of the user so that we can send emails to them if required.

attributes.name: PhoneNumber
attributes.caption: Phone Number
attributes.documentation: The phone number of the user.

attributes.name: Level
attributes.caption: Level
attributes.documentation: Only used for simple version of security roles

attributes.name: Preferences
attributes.caption: Preferences
attributes.documentation: e.g. lasttemplate=45;lastdate=2007-09-01;blah1=2;blah2=3

classes.name: WebAction
classes.caption: WebAction
classes.documentation: This holds the information about each web action

attributes.name: Name
attributes.caption: Name
attributes.documentation: e.g. employer_applicationlist

attributes.name: Title
attributes.caption: Title
attributes.documentation: User displayable action name. e.g. "List of Employer's applications"

attributes.name: Introduction
attributes.caption: Introduction
attributes.documentation: This can be used to place a small piece of content at the top of the page.

attributes.name: Footer
attributes.caption: Footer
attributes.documentation: This can be used to place a small piece of content at the bottom of the page.

attributes.name: SecurityLevel
attributes.caption: Security Level
attributes.documentation: Min security level required to execute this action

attributes.name: Size
attributes.caption: Size
attributes.documentation: This is the estimated size /earned value

attributes.name: ActionGroup
attributes.caption: Action Group
attributes.documentation: Allows us to group actions for planning and reporting

attributes.name: ProgrammedDate
attributes.caption: Programmed Date
attributes.documentation: This is the date the taks was handed to QA.

attributes.name: SignoffDate
attributes.caption: Signoff Date
attributes.documentation: This is the date that QA signed off the webaction

attributes.name: SignoffContentDate
attributes.caption: Signoff Content Date
attributes.documentation: This is when the content has been signed off.

attributes.name: Description
attributes.caption: Description
attributes.documentation: This is the hoverhint for any menu items for this action.

attributes.name: Style
attributes.caption: Style
attributes.documentation: Used for indicating what format is used

attributes.name: Parameters
attributes.caption: Parameters
attributes.documentation: This allows us some default processing

attributes.name: WeekNo
attributes.caption: Week No
attributes.documentation: This is the planned weekno to complete this task

classes.name: Arc
classes.caption: Arc
classes.documentation: An arc links a place to a transition.

attributes.name: ArcType
attributes.caption: Arc Type
attributes.documentation: {sequential,and-split,and-join,or-split,or-join,xor-split}

classes.name: Case
classes.caption: Case
classes.documentation: This holds the context and current status of a particular piece of work going through a workflow.

attributes.name: CaseStatus
attributes.caption: Case Status
attributes.documentation: {Open,Closed,Held,Cancelled}

classes.name: Place
classes.caption: Place
classes.documentation: This holds the details of each place within a workflow. i.e. State within a state engine.

classes.name: Token
classes.caption: Token
classes.documentation: This indicates that a piece of work is in a particular place.

attributes.name: token_status
attributes.caption: Token Status
attributes.documentation: {Enabled,Locked,Cancelled,Consumed}

classes.name: Transition
classes.caption: Transition
classes.documentation: This holds the details for each transition within a workflow process. It points to the application task witin the menu database.

attributes.name: Triggertype
attributes.caption: Trigger Type
attributes.documentation: {Automatic,User,Time,Message}

classes.name: Workflow

classes.documentation:
This holds the definition for each workflow process.
e.g. Fulfill order.

classes.documentation: This indicates when a transition is enabled and ready to fire.

attributes.name: Triggertype
attributes.caption: Trigger Type
attributes.documentation: {user,auto,message,time}
